Kt/V calculation based on a single pool urea model neglects compartmental urea distribution in the body, hence PDUR, resulting in overestimation of actual Kt/V. Therefore, a two pool model should be applied, using instead of the urea plasma concentration at the end of the dialysis, the equilibrated urea, i.e. 60 min postdialysis [65, 66]. Other improvements from the initial formula are proposed to provide a more accurate Kt/V calculation: weight loss (UF/BW) and urea generation during the dialysis session (0.008td), leading to the Daugirdas and Schwartz formula proposed in 1994 [60]:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
